
DokuWiki

[%image%](http://www.dokuwiki.org/wiki%3Adokuwiki) DokuWiki is a standards compliant, simple to use [Wiki](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki), mainly aimed at creating documentation of any kind. It is targeted at developer teams, workgroups and small companies. It has a simple but powerful [Formatting Syntax](../wiki/syntax.html) which makes sure the datafiles remain readable outside the Wiki and eases the creation of structured texts. All data is stored in plain text files – no database is required.

Read the [DokuWiki Manual](http://www.dokuwiki.org/manual) to unleash the full power of DokuWiki.

